The 60-year-old Afraha Stadium is set to undergo massive refurbishment to upgrade it into international standards in three phases. The first phase is estimated to cost Sh650million and will see the stadium have a sitting capacity of 20,000 people. Ulinzi Stars have shifted their Football Kenya Federation Premier League home matches from their traditional Afraha Stadium in Nakuru to Kericho Green Stadium.
Kericho Green Stadium is the home ground of Zoo FC and they will now share the facility with the soldiers. Afraha Stadium is set to undergo renovations for the next 60 weeks.



